21:56.817 --> 21:58.279
He can't stop anything he wants to.

21:59.201 --> 22:00.242
So when the plane

22:00.514 --> 22:13.606
flew into the tower on 9-11, all he had to do would go, and that plane misses the tower by 60 feet, and you saved 2,000 people.

22:13.626 --> 22:14.747
You think he could not do that?

22:15.909 --> 22:18.731
He governs the wind and the waves, the Bible says.

22:18.851 --> 22:22.054
So he can stop anything he wants from happening.

22:22.255 --> 22:24.236
If he doesn't stop it, he wills it to happen.

22:26.018 --> 22:28.180
That's the will of God sovereignly.

22:28.300 --> 22:30.162
But here's another use of the word will.

22:31.906 --> 22:39.394
For this is the will of God, your sanctification, that you abstain from sexual immorality.

22:42.116 --> 22:45.059
So a student comes to me and asks me, what's the will of God for my life?

22:45.119 --> 22:46.501
I know the will of God for your life.

22:46.881 --> 22:48.823
It's sanctification.

22:48.923 --> 22:50.885
That's the will of God for your life, holiness.

22:51.165 --> 22:52.607
Stay out of bed with your girlfriend.

22:53.007 --> 22:54.649
That's the will of God for your life.

22:55.290 --> 22:59.634
And he can disobey that and break the will of God.

23:00.450 --> 23:02.152
cancel the will of God in his life.

23:02.552 --> 23:06.136
So that's clearly not the same meaning as the will of God in the first case.

23:06.216 --> 23:13.883
So you've got two meanings of will of God and that's utterly crucial as you come to that phrase over and over again.

23:13.943 --> 23:15.685
So what does it mean here?

23:17.086 --> 23:17.707
Don't be foolish.

23:18.328 --> 23:20.530
Understand what the will of the Lord is.

23:22.311 --> 23:26.796
You're not required to know the sovereign will of God.

23:27.136 --> 23:27.837
You don't know it.

23:28.257 --> 23:28.978
I don't know it.

23:29.474 --> 23:31.276
you're not held responsible to know it.

23:31.717 --> 23:39.085
But you are responsible to know the revealed will of God, like the Ten Commandments or the Sermon on the Mount or Romans 12.

23:40.567 --> 23:42.389
And that's what we're supposed to do.

23:42.409 --> 23:54.322
And the reason you need the Holy Spirit is because in your day, just think of this, my guess is you have thought about it, even if you haven't articulated it, you've experienced it.

23:55.554 --> 24:00.121
You read your Bible in the morning and you see maybe five or 10 things, it says you should do.

24:01.103 --> 24:04.328
And then you make about a thousand choices during the day.

24:05.370 --> 24:10.458
Like this left hand of mine is in the air, but I did not think about that.

24:10.598 --> 24:11.259
It's just there.

24:13.903 --> 24:22.076
So there are a thousand decisions that you make.

24:22.096 --> 24:23.218
Which of those should you make?

24:23.586 --> 24:26.069
Let me just guess.

24:26.089 --> 24:31.176
98% of them are not stipulated in the Bible.

24:35.022 --> 24:39.388
Well, how do I know what to do?

24:41.491 --> 24:43.053
Kiss my wife goodbye when I go?

24:43.093 --> 24:45.296
Yeah, not in the Bible.

24:46.117 --> 24:48.260
Well, kind of is.

24:50.022 --> 24:52.786
You've got any sense at all.

24:56.130 --> 24:57.712
and many, many such things.

24:59.675 --> 25:06.146
You need to be filled with the Holy Spirit because the Holy Spirit conforms you to Christ.

25:07.908 --> 25:09.691
He saturates you with the Word.

25:09.751 --> 25:11.253
He exalts Jesus.

25:12.856 --> 25:21.970
He weaves together implications of texts and you sense his leading into

25:22.370 --> 25:24.613
Yeah, kiss your wife for goodness sake.

25:24.693 --> 25:25.654
You love her.

25:26.215 --> 25:27.516
She would love that.

25:27.536 --> 25:29.879
Don't just walk out and go to Dallas.

25:39.992 --> 25:41.073
Now we're at the sing part.

25:44.398 --> 25:47.922
Don't get drunk with wine for that is debauchery, but be filled with the spirit.

25:52.098 --> 25:56.383
Addressing one another, they're four participles.

25:58.746 --> 26:01.329
So be filled with the Holy Spirit is the main verb here.

26:03.932 --> 26:19.410
And then you got addressing one another with Psalms in hymns and spiritual songs, singing, making melody to the Lord with your heart, giving thanks always and for everything to God, to Father.

26:19.586 --> 26:25.032
in the name of the Lord Jesus, and it goes on submitting to one another, but I left that out because we can't do everything.

26:25.312 --> 26:31.399
So they're really our five part of sipples, and we're only gonna talk about the musical ones here.

26:33.941 --> 26:36.384
Let's start with giving thanks.

26:40.328 --> 26:41.389
This is really amazing.

26:41.950 --> 26:45.874
If I tried to, if I could write the list down here, I won't take the time to do it.

26:46.050 --> 26:52.979
my list again, put four things in the list, addressing, singing, making melody, giving thanks.

26:54.642 --> 26:58.807
Giving thanks is the internal one here.

27:00.209 --> 27:01.671
Singing is out loud.

27:01.811 --> 27:03.974
It's what you do with your lips and it's voice.

27:04.294 --> 27:09.161
Making melody is addressing one another is, but it's giving thanks, or at least experiencing thanks.

27:10.403 --> 27:12.946
Being a thankful person is inside.

27:13.442 --> 27:21.454
And it says, giving thanks always, hazing always, and for everything.

27:21.795 --> 27:23.177
Doesn't it say in everything?

27:23.237 --> 27:25.781
It says in everything in First Thessalonians.

27:26.081 --> 27:34.914
It says for everything, which is simply wild and crazy and great.

27:34.934 --> 27:35.275
Really?

27:35.836 --> 27:42.706
I mean, you just heard a great message from David Mathis about the place of grief and sorrow

27:45.218 --> 27:48.042
to give thanks for all of those.

27:52.348 --> 28:13.298
In order for that to be true eventually, if not in the moment emotionally, when the terrible, terrible, horrible news comes, in order for that to be true, you have to have a very, very high view of the wisdom of God and the goodness of God and the power of God.

28:14.306 --> 28:21.256
How else can you give thanks for the bad things that happen in your life?

28:25.402 --> 28:29.188
Which is why I think it is foundational to all singing.

28:31.351 --> 28:39.383
A belief in the sovereign wisdom and goodness and power of God is essential for all worship.

28:39.403 --> 28:41.586
At least worship in a real world of horror.

28:43.362 --> 28:52.971
I mean, I guess is that the world who's aware of the horror in the world looks at Christians singing on Sunday morning, those people have their head in the sand.

28:53.252 --> 28:55.274
I mean, this is the most ridiculous thing I've ever seen.

28:55.294 --> 28:58.137
They sing, they sing like they're in paradise.

28:58.677 --> 28:59.358
No, we don't.

29:00.299 --> 29:07.446
We always have tears on our faces when we sing, always, because we always know somebody's in pain.

29:07.886 --> 29:08.887
We always have a kid.

29:08.907 --> 29:11.890
We wish we're different than he is.

29:12.226 --> 29:15.250
We always know the person down in the pews walking through hell.

29:15.710 --> 29:16.812
We always know.

29:16.832 --> 29:18.834
We're not fools.

29:18.894 --> 29:19.896
We're not idiots.

29:21.578 --> 29:30.449
But we know God is good and God is strong and God is wise and God has his purposes and that's why we can sing.

29:32.011 --> 29:41.042
So I think with Paul saying, giving thanks always and for everything is his way of saying

29:41.186 --> 29:45.572
Your father is good to you.

29:46.774 --> 29:49.457
He doesn't give a stone to those who ask for bread.

29:49.518 --> 29:56.587
He may not give the bread that you're asking for, but he's not a father who's contemptuous towards his children.

29:57.068 --> 29:59.551
He always has our good at his heart.

30:00.032 --> 30:04.358
And he does so in the name of the Lord because Jesus Christ has died for us.

30:05.179 --> 30:10.066
God designed it that way so that everything could work together for sinners like us.

30:11.650 --> 30:21.139
Then you back up to addressing one another in Psalms and hymns and spiritual songs and singing and making melody.

30:21.179 --> 30:31.850
So you have three kinds of songs, namely songs, hymns and spiritual songs.

30:32.831 --> 30:37.175
And you have two kinds of singing, singing, making melody.

30:38.716 --> 30:40.338
And I've read a lot of commentaries.

30:40.994 --> 30:43.077
And nobody knows what this means.

30:46.762 --> 30:49.747
I mean, everybody knows what it means.

30:51.309 --> 30:55.815
But nobody knows the precise distinctions between these three words.

30:56.676 --> 30:59.641
You just go ahead, pick a commentary and read it, and they're all guessing.

31:00.963 --> 31:05.429
It might be that Psalms refers to the 150 Psalms in the Bible.

31:06.070 --> 31:08.914
Hymns refer to formal guts.

31:09.378 --> 31:13.785
more or less formal songs about God and spiritual songs.

31:14.205 --> 31:20.795
This being the very broad word for songs would be spontaneous songs that have come to people's minds.

31:21.296 --> 31:27.485
I've had several people sing spontaneous songs over me, like spirit given in the moment songs.

31:27.766 --> 31:28.467
Very moving.

31:29.729 --> 31:32.593
You wouldn't sing them in worship because they're usually not very melodic.

31:33.835 --> 31:37.260
That's just the way it is when you're spontaneously singing.

31:37.481 --> 31:38.482
But in the moment,

31:38.594 --> 31:40.957
It's very powerful, very beautiful thing.

31:42.619 --> 31:43.580
So we just don't know.

31:43.761 --> 31:54.414
So what we do know is that's a lot of options, meaning cover the ground, cover the field with your singing.

31:54.474 --> 32:00.702
Yeah, do the Psalms, do the spiritual choruses, do the hymns.

32:00.802 --> 32:07.090
I mean, if we were to lay it on the contemporary scene, those present realities would not

32:07.202 --> 32:12.609
probably be far off from Paul saying, don't be stuck.

32:12.629 --> 32:15.372
I think to be a Psalms-only church is probably a mistake.

32:15.432 --> 32:16.514
Don't want to offend anybody.

32:17.435 --> 32:19.077
I love singing the Psalms.

32:19.177 --> 32:20.559
The Trinity hymnal is great.

32:20.639 --> 32:21.680
The Psalter is great.

32:21.780 --> 32:22.942
Everything is great.

32:22.962 --> 32:24.103
It's Godward.

32:25.285 --> 32:28.949
And that's why we have to be filled with the Holy Spirit.

32:29.290 --> 32:32.594
Because I think the Holy Spirit gives the

32:32.866 --> 32:38.273
ground and the shaping and the goal to our singing so that it doesn't get off base.

32:38.293 --> 32:40.757
It doesn't go crazy theologically.

32:42.799 --> 32:47.946
So Psalms and hymns and spiritual songs and then singing and making melody.

32:49.348 --> 32:50.910
You know, I have somewhere in here.

32:53.353 --> 32:54.054
Where did I put it?

32:56.398 --> 32:56.558
Yeah.

33:00.143 --> 33:01.725
Singing and making melody.

33:01.745 --> 33:02.706
Those are Greek words.

33:02.850 --> 33:05.554
That's for two or three of you anyway.

33:08.519 --> 33:09.059
Same thing.

33:09.200 --> 33:12.244
These two words, this means singing and this means singing.

33:15.749 --> 33:21.398
And the translators mix it up because that would sound funny.

33:22.079 --> 33:25.003
If you said spiritual songs, singing and singing.

33:26.305 --> 33:28.088
So they say singing and making many.

33:28.108 --> 33:29.490
Because they are different words.

33:29.762 --> 33:36.471
And if we knew more, if we had more uses of the words, we might be able to make clear distinctions between them.

33:36.531 --> 33:38.533
But they're used throughout the rest of the New Testament.

33:38.553 --> 33:40.195
And as far as I can tell, I'm looking them all up.

33:41.217 --> 33:53.532
There are no distinctions between them that I can make out, which means that I think gives us permission to sing in various ways.

33:53.592 --> 33:56.116
There are all kinds of ways to sing.

33:56.156 --> 33:57.938
So here's what is

33:58.946 --> 34:05.435
special about these words that we need to pay attention to, addressing one another.

34:05.996 --> 34:07.558
That's significant.

34:08.840 --> 34:11.623
And making melody to the Lord.

34:11.924 --> 34:12.725
Well, which is it?

34:15.529 --> 34:19.534
Addressing one another as we sing or singing to the Lord.

34:20.856 --> 34:22.899
And then thirdly, from your heart.

34:23.780 --> 34:27.986
Those three phrases are massively important to think about when you're

34:28.290 --> 34:31.018
planning how to sing with a group.

34:31.038 --> 34:40.404
And the first one singing to one another is what we did in the first two songs when we sang tonight, right?

34:41.307 --> 34:43.794
For example, here's

34:44.290 --> 34:46.172
Come Christians, join to sing.

34:46.733 --> 34:48.495
Hallelujah, amen.

34:48.976 --> 34:50.758
Loud praise to Christ our King.

34:51.079 --> 34:52.501
Hallelujah, amen.

34:52.981 --> 34:56.386
Let all with heart and voice be for His throne rejoice.

34:56.406 --> 34:58.268
Praise His gracious choice.

34:58.288 --> 34:59.450
Hallelujah, amen.

34:59.690 --> 35:00.691
I'm saying that to you.

35:00.771 --> 35:02.494
Come on.

35:02.514 --> 35:03.054
You didn't come.

35:04.717 --> 35:05.197
You didn't come.

35:05.598 --> 35:07.220
Come Christians, join to sing.

35:07.700 --> 35:09.963
So that's to one another, right?

35:10.344 --> 35:11.986
And then you have songs like

35:12.258 --> 35:14.161
Great is thy faithfulness.

35:14.602 --> 35:15.623
Oh, God, my father.

35:15.683 --> 35:18.187
Seeing that straight to him.

35:18.648 --> 35:24.357
I mean, I'm so biased in my own preference for that kind of singing that I'm changing words all the time while we're singing.

35:24.377 --> 35:26.901
Is he worthy?

35:26.961 --> 35:27.802
Are you worthy?

35:27.863 --> 35:28.524
Are you worthy?

35:28.564 --> 35:30.767
Yes, you are worthy.

35:30.787 --> 35:33.291
I can hardly let myself say he.

35:33.311 --> 35:36.336
I love that song.

35:36.356 --> 35:37.798
He or he or you, either way.

35:39.120 --> 35:40.242
But here's the thing.

35:40.418 --> 35:46.366
So if you're supposed to do both, is he saying, sometimes you do one, sometimes you do the other?

35:48.048 --> 35:48.549
I don't think so.

35:50.832 --> 35:55.499
I think in a corporate setting with two or more people, you're always doing both.

35:56.800 --> 35:59.905
God is always listening to your songs, right?

36:00.726 --> 36:01.867
Always listening to your songs.

36:01.887 --> 36:09.618
So you are, if you have any awareness of that fact, singing before him, to him, even if you're singing to each other.

36:10.562 --> 36:15.229
And if you're singing to him, you know this person right here is listening to you.

36:16.290 --> 36:24.442
He's aware that you're singing to him, which means you're aware that he's aware of your singing to him and therefore you're addressing him.

36:25.564 --> 36:26.726
I see this is just huge.

36:27.487 --> 36:38.002
In my life, I've stood as a pastor for 33 years and now 12 years since then in corporate worship as

36:38.914 --> 36:41.617
just about the favorite hour of my week.

36:41.637 --> 36:43.299
I don't even think I need to say just about.

36:43.919 --> 36:47.343
I love corporate worship.

36:47.363 --> 36:47.904
I love it.

36:49.345 --> 36:51.507
Something happens to me in corporate worship.

36:51.528 --> 36:58.915
Something happens when in our church, maybe 500 people in the service, lift their voices.

36:59.676 --> 37:03.320
The instruments don't drown them out, and talk about that later in the Q&A.

37:04.682 --> 37:08.786
The instruments don't drown them out because God loves corporate voices singing.

37:08.930 --> 37:14.338
And we sing, and the emotion of those people changes me.

37:15.540 --> 37:21.108
It does, and it's designed to, the spiritual affections rising.

37:21.469 --> 37:26.597
And you can tell that some of them are bored stiff, and you don't pay any attention to them.

37:26.657 --> 37:33.107
That's between them and God, they got issues, and they need to be here too.

37:33.728 --> 37:36.892
But you're not looking at them.

37:36.952 --> 37:38.034
You're looking at that.

37:38.530 --> 37:46.481
that old lady just lost her husband, and you just came back from a year away, and she's there with her little baggy, skinny arm here.

37:46.501 --> 37:55.994
She's 80 years old, and she's got her hand up like this, singing her husband's in the grave for 12 months, and she's still singing, and everything in here says, yes!

37:57.056 --> 37:57.376
Right?

37:57.396 --> 37:57.857
Yes!

37:59.419 --> 38:05.668
I mean, corporate worship is designed to be utterly transformative for a church.

38:06.049 --> 38:07.090
It's designed to

38:07.362 --> 38:22.741
to draw people like me in, you've been crabby with your wife, right, on the way to church or the night before, and you're singing now of the sweet mercies of God and his patience towards you, and you are broken.

38:23.182 --> 38:24.303
And she's standing right here.

38:26.906 --> 38:31.112
And you say, I'm an idiot.

38:31.692 --> 38:36.338
Why in view of this glory is that little

38:36.418 --> 38:39.982
niggling thing wrecking this relationship.

38:40.623 --> 38:42.224
And your whole world is fixed.

38:42.264 --> 38:44.747
It's just fixed in a moment, right?

38:45.648 --> 38:48.832
That's happened to me over and over again.

38:49.192 --> 38:52.976
And with Tom Steller, my associate for 33 years, is down the road.

38:53.016 --> 38:54.978
And I'm thinking about my message.

38:55.038 --> 38:55.899
And am I ready?

38:55.959 --> 38:58.322
And are the people going to like the message?

38:58.382 --> 39:01.465
And I'll just self absorb stuff.

39:02.406 --> 39:03.588
And I happen to glance down there.

39:03.888 --> 39:05.810
And there's Tom in the third heaven.

39:10.946 --> 39:13.168
That is a total gift to me.

39:14.189 --> 39:17.453
It is a total rebuke to me and a gift.

39:17.733 --> 39:18.434
Come on, Piper.

39:18.754 --> 39:19.896
Forget about yourself.

39:19.996 --> 39:20.757
Get into this.

39:21.037 --> 39:22.038
This is about God.

39:22.058 --> 39:22.999
It's not about you.

39:24.701 --> 39:34.111
So addressing one another in spiritual songs and doing it to the Lord are not alternatives.

39:34.832 --> 39:36.393
They're both happening all the time.

39:36.513 --> 39:40.818
And maybe the last thing to say would be from the heart.

39:40.962 --> 39:52.360
looking for my original slide, whereas there it is, from your heart, with your heart.

39:52.380 --> 39:56.987
Jesus said, this people honors me with their lips, but their heart is far from me.

39:58.570 --> 40:08.946
So the job of a pastor and a worship leader is to do everything we can in prayer and design and the feast of the word to help people

40:11.234 --> 40:14.457
wake up, that their hearts come alive.

40:16.299 --> 40:21.664
I don't think it's worship if it's just words or just hands in the air.

40:22.425 --> 40:24.867
You can put your hands in the air and sleep with your girlfriend at night.

40:26.008 --> 40:26.529
It happens.

40:28.050 --> 40:29.051
That's not worship.

40:30.112 --> 40:33.755
That stinks in God's nose, says so in the Bible.

40:35.397 --> 40:39.961
So it really matters that we cultivate with your heart.

40:40.021 --> 40:40.722
So let me end.

40:40.994 --> 40:54.308
Okay, if fullness of the Holy Spirit be filled with the Spirit is the key to that, all of that, how do you get filled with the Holy Spirit?

40:55.129 --> 40:58.513
And I'll give you just three steps that I think are biblical.

40:58.673 --> 40:59.934
Number one, pray for it.

41:00.615 --> 41:01.876
That's how I began tonight, right?

41:02.237 --> 41:03.058
I ask for it.

41:03.618 --> 41:07.122
I ask that God would fill us with the Holy Spirit.

41:07.394 --> 41:13.824
If you then who are evil know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will they have any father give the Holy Spirit to those who ask him?

41:14.044 --> 41:14.805
That's Christians.

41:15.606 --> 41:18.290
It's not the unbeliever asking to get the Holy Spirit.

41:18.310 --> 41:24.419
That's Christians asking for a greater measure of the Holy Spirit, just like here in Ephesians.

41:24.840 --> 41:34.354
I pray, this is Paul praying, that according to the riches of his glory, he may grant you to be strengthened with power through his spirit in your inner being.

41:34.850 --> 41:37.753
so that Christ may dwell in your heart through faith.

41:39.655 --> 41:54.071
So this greater indwelling, this greater empowering, this greater control, this greater experience of the Holy Spirit comes through faith, just like it says here in Galatians.

41:55.813 --> 42:03.701
Does He who supplies the Spirit to you and works miracles among you do so by works of the law?

42:03.761 --> 42:04.562
No.

42:05.794 --> 42:10.440
or by hearing with faith, yes, hearing with faith.

42:10.680 --> 42:11.441
Hearing what?

42:12.603 --> 42:14.004
And that's the last step.

42:14.925 --> 42:18.009
Faith comes from hearing and hearing through the Word of God.

42:18.130 --> 42:34.450
I don't know any other way to help you walk by the Spirit or be filled by the Spirit than to say, get up in the morning and say, God, please, I feel very dry, even guilty.

42:35.042 --> 42:36.204
I need to be cleansed.

42:36.264 --> 42:37.145
I need to be forgiven.

42:37.285 --> 42:42.774
And I pray that you wash me clean and that you'd come now and fill me with the Holy Spirit.

42:42.814 --> 42:45.538
So when I go to the breakfast table, I can be of some use to my family.

42:46.079 --> 42:48.242
Fill me with the Holy Spirit.

42:48.642 --> 42:54.111
And then secondly, you turn to a word of God.

42:56.053 --> 42:56.734
I will help you.

42:56.995 --> 42:57.876
I will strengthen you.

42:58.597 --> 43:04.466
I'll hold you up with my victorious right hand and you believe it.

43:04.546 --> 43:05.307
three steps.

43:05.867 --> 43:13.115
Pray, look at the Word, and believe in the Holy Spirit moves through the Word by the belief.

43:19.682 --> 43:22.525
I think we'll save these because a lot of time is up.

43:23.306 --> 43:31.314
I've got about eight controversial statements tonight, but maybe in the Q&A we'll see.

43:31.522 --> 43:41.895
Let me pray, and I'll let the powers that be make that call.

43:41.916 --> 43:43.518
Father, you have met us.

43:43.538 --> 43:44.439
You've helped us.

43:46.602 --> 43:59.218
